  "texts": [
    "The use of transformer-based Large Language Models (LLMs), such as BERT (Devlin et al., 2019), is now well-established in both AES (Rodriguez et al., 2019; Uto & Uchida, 2020; Yang et al., 2020) and ASAS (C. Ormerod, 2022).",
    "In the past few years, GLMs like ChatGPT (OpenAI, 2023) have garnered immense attention from both the media and academic circles.",
    "These GLMs are pretrained on a large corpus and then instruction-tuned to perform a multitude of tasks (Chung et al., 2022).Attempts at ATS with GLMs have focused primarily on large, proprietary models (Mizumoto & Eguchi, 2023), which raises several concerns in an educational setting.",
    "Firstly, given that student data can include personally identifiable information, the reliance on an externally managed API poses a security risk.",
    "Secondly, since the model weights are not publicly available, there is no ability to apply tools from explainable AI (xAI) (Linardatos et al., 2021)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}